        "answer_count": 2,
        "title": "Using query parameter of type not supported in Spring Data JDBC?",
        "body": "<p>I tried to write a query method in my repository similar to this<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>@Modifying\n@Query(\"UPDATE foo SET some_timestamp = :someTimestamp WHERE id = :id\")\nvoid updateSomeTimestamp(@Param(\"id\") long id, @Param(\"someTimestamp\") Instant someTimestamp)\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>When executing the code I got the following error:<\/p>\n\n<p><em>org.postgresql.util.PSQLException: Can't infer the SQL type to use for an instance of java.time.Instant. Use setObject() with an explicit Types value to specify the type to use.<\/em><\/p>\n\n<p>Did I forget something or is usage of Instant as parameter simply not supported by Spring Data Jdbc? If so, is such a support planned in the future?<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 59404071,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "spring",
            "type-conversion",
            "spring-data",
            "spring-data-jdbc"
        ],
        "score": 4,
        "accepted_answer_id": 59404260,
